 34CL    33S(P,P),(P,P'G):RESONANCES   1989VA15,1964VA12         ENSDF    202609
 34CL  H TYP=FUL$AUT=LIJIE SUN AND JUN CHEN$CIT=ENSDF$CUT=30-Sep-2026$          
 34CL  H TYP=FUL$AUT=NINEL NICA, BALRAJ SINGH$CIT=NDS 113, 1563 (2012)$         
 34CL2 H CUT=28-May-2012$                                                       
 34CL c  {+33}S+1p|){+34}Cl from J|p=3/2+ {+33}S ground state.                  
 34CL c  1989Va15: 1.2-3.77-MeV proton beams from the 4-MV Van de Graaff        
 34CL2c  accelerator at TUNL impinged on a Ag{-2}S target 88.2% enriched in     
 34CL3c  {+33}S. Measured differential cross sections for {+33}S(p,p{-0}),      
 34CL4c  {+33}S(p,p{-1}), and {+33}S(p,p{-2}). Extracted resonance parameters   
 34CL5c  for 144 levels by fitting the excitation functions with a multilevel,  
 34CL6c  multichannel R-matrix model.                                           
 34CL c  1964Va12: 1.2-3.2-MeV proton beams from the Utrecht 3-MV Van de Graaff 
 34CL2c  accelerator impinged on CdS targets 22%-enriched in {+33}S. |g rays    
 34CL3c  were detected using a cylindrical NaI(Tl) detector. Measured |g-ray    
 34CL4c  yields and deduced 44 levels via the {+33}S(p,p'|g) reaction.          
 34CL cL E$E(level)=E{-c.m.}+S(p)({+34}Cl) where S(p)({+34}Cl)=5143.20 {I5}     
 34CL2cL (2021Wa16) and E{-c.m.}=E{-p}(lab)|*m({+33}S)/[m{-p}+m({+33}S)].       
 34CL3cL E{-p}(lab) is from 1989Va15, unless otherwise noted. 1989Va15 states   
 34CL4cL that the calibrations provide accurate energies of |DE=|+300 eV near   
 34CL5cL the calibration points and a maximum error of |DE=|+1.5 keV away from  
 34CL6cL the calibration points. The calibration points are at E(p)=1.8804 MeV  
 34CL7cL and 3.2357 MeV. Therefore, the evaluators assign a |DE=0.3 keV for     
 34CL8cL levels within 100 keV of either calibration point, and a |DE=1.5 keV   
 34CL9cL for other levels.                                                      
 34CL cL J,T,L$From 1989Va15 multilevel, multichannel R-matrix analysis.        
 34CL2cL 1989Va15 states that typical uncertainties are 10% for laboratory      
 34CL3cL widths of a few keV or smaller, and 20% for the larger widths of tens  
 34CL4cL of keV. Reduced width |g{+2}=|G/2P, where |G is the laboratory width   
 34CL5cL and P is the Coulomb penetrability (1989Va15).                         
